{"title_page": "National Board of Review Awards 1997", "text_new": "<div style=\"float: right; font-size: smaller; background-color:#E6E6FA; padding: 12px; margin-left: 5em; margin-bottom: 2em; width: 180px\" align=\"center\">\n\n<big>'''69th National Board of Review Awards'''</big><br>\n<div style=\"padding-left: 15px\">\nDecember 8, 1998\n</div>\n----\nBest Picture: <br>\n<big>''' L.A. Confidential '''</big>\n</div>\nThe '''69th National Board of Review Awards''', honoring the best in filmmaking in [[1997 in film|1997]], were announced on 9 December 1997 and given on 9 February 1998.\n\n==Top 10 films==\n#''[[L.A. Confidential (film)|L.A. Confidential]]''\n#''[[As Good as It Gets]]''\n#''[[The Wings of the Dove (1997 film)|The Wings of the Dove]]''\n#''[[Good Will Hunting]]''\n#''[[Titanic (1997 film)|Titanic]]''\n#''[[The Sweet Hereafter (film)|The Sweet Hereafter]]''\n#''[[Boogie Nights]]''\n#''[[The Full Monty]]''\n#''[[The Rainmaker (1997 film)|The Rainmaker]]''\n#''[[Jackie Brown (film)|Jackie Brown]]''\n\n==Top Foreign Films==\n#''[[Shall We Dance? (1996 film)|Shall We Dance?]]''\n#''[[Beaumarchais, l'insolent]]''\n#''[[Ma vie en rose]]''\n#''[[La Promesse]]''\n#''[[Ponette]]''\n\n==Winners==\n*Best Picture:\n**''[[L.A. Confidential (film)|L.A. Confidential]]''\n*Best Foreign Film:\n**''[[Shall We Dance? (1996 film)|Shall We Dance?]]''\n*Best Actor:\n**[[Jack Nicholson]] - ''[[As Good as It Gets]]''\n*Best Actress:\n**[[Helena Bonham Carter]] - ''[[The Wings of the Dove (1997 film)|The Wings of the Dove]]''\n*Best Supporting Actor:\n**[[Greg Kinnear]] - ''[[As Good as It Gets]]''\n*Best Supporting Actress:\n**[[Anne Heche]] - ''[[Donnie Brasco (film)|Donnie Brasco]]'', ''[[Wag the Dog]]''\n*Best Acting by an Ensemble\n**''[[The Sweet Hereafter (film)|The Sweet Hereafter]]''\n*Breakthrough Performance:\n**[[Bai Ling]] - ''[[Red Corner]]''\n*Best Director:\n**[[Curtis Hanson]] - ''[[L.A. Confidential (film)|L.A. Confidential]]''\n*Outstanding Directorial Debut