\n| music           =\n| platforms       = [[Nintendo Switch]]\n| released        = TBA<ref name=\"delayed\" />\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = Shironeko Project Hikoujima Kouen\n| author          = Colopl\n| illustrator     = Tsurujirou Matsudaira\n| publisher       = [[Kodansha]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| magazine        = Comic Clear\n| first           = July 2017\n| last            = July 2018\n| volumes         = 3\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| title           = Zero Chronicle\n| director        = Masato Jinbo\n| producer        = \n| writer          = Masato Jinbo\n| music           = [[Taku Iwasaki]]\n| studio          = [[Project No.9]]\n| network         = [[AT-X (company)|AT-X]], [[Tokyo MX]], [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]]\n| licensee        = [[Funimation]]\n| first           = April 6, 2020\n| last            = scheduled\n| episodes        = \n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = Zero Chronicle\n\n| author          = Yuichi Tobiyama\n\n| illustrator     = Fuku Kitsune\n\n| publisher       = [[Kadokawa Shoten]]\n\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| magazine        =\n| first           = April 1. 2020\n| last            =\n| volumes         = 1\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''White Cat Project'''''|\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8|Shironeko Purojekuto}} is a [[free-to-play]] [[action role-playing game]] developed and published by Colopl for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]]. It was initially released in Japan on July 14, 2014. An English-language version was released internationally under the name '''''Colopl Rune Story''''' and operated from July 23, 2015, to October 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Suckley |first1=Matt |title=COLOPL NI winds up development on JRPG Rune Story after just one year |url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/asia/news/64298/colopl-ni-winds-up-development-on-rune-story/ |website=[[Pocket Gamer|Pocket Gamer.biz]]|date=October 28, 2016 |accessdate=11 November 2018}}</ref> A spinoff title, {{Nihongo|'''''White Cat Tennis'''''|\u767d\u732b\u30c6\u30cb\u30b9|Shironeko Tenisu}} was released on both iOS and Android on July 31, 2016, while the upcoming sequel '''''Shironeko New Project''''' will be released on the [[Nintendo Switch]] at a later date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/07/13/white-cat-project-is-getting-a-brand-new-title-for-nintendo-switch-in-2020/|title=White Cat Project Is Getting A Brand-New Title For Nintendo Switch In 2020|last=Sato|date=2018-07-13|website=Siliconera|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref>\n\nAn [[anime]] adaptation of the game's 3rd anniversary event is produced by [[Project No.9]] and set to premiere in April 6, 2020.\n\n==Plot==\nA long time ago, there is an ancient legend revolving around two figures, the White Maiden of the Sky; represented by the White Cat, and the Black Prince of Darkness; represented by the Black Cat. At the same time, a war between the demons and the guardians of light took place, with the demons led by the Black King of Darkness attacking the lands in the sky. The Black Prince however, despite the wishes of the Black King, defied his orders and falls in love with the White Maiden, in hopes that their union would end the war. Both were not meant to meet and love each other as the war ravaged the world around the land and the skies.\n\nSeveral millennia after the war, in a world consisting of numerous isles, a young hero from the Astora Isle encounters the adventurer Kyle and follows him on an expedition on the isle. They meet a mysterious girl named Iris and a talking white cat named Catra, and together they make their way to the isle's ruins, where they find a flying island. Kyle becomes consumed by darkness there, and the party resolves to travel to the ends of the world on the flying island in order to find the seven \"Great Runes\", following Kyle's words before he disappeared.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc\uff5c\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8 \u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8 |url=https://colopl.co.jp/shironekoproject/character/ |website=Colopl |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja}}</ref> Upon their adventures towards finding the Runes, both the hero and Iris start to fill the pieces, meeting friends and enemies and discovering their true identities.\n\n==Gameplay==\n''White Cat Project'' is an [[action role-playing game]] with [[touchscreen]] controls, where the player controls the character by dragging the finger across the screen (a mechanic Colopl calls \"Punicon\") and tapping to attack. Special abilities can be activated by holding the finger on the character, which opens up a selection menu of abilities. All of these actions can be done using one finger only, which facilitates one-handed gaming.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Eugene |title=White Cat Project Is An Action RPG Played With Just Your Thumb |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2014/07/12/white-cat-project-action-rpg-played-just-thumb/ |website=[[Siliconera]] |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=12 July 2014}}</ref>  \n\nThe characters also have their own classes corresponding to weapon types, for example swords, bows, and mage staffs. In general, most characters are gained via a \"Summon\" tab which works on a [[Gacha game|gacha]] system. Runes are spent on randomized characters, with some characters being common and other characters being rare.  Some characters can be gained for free by completing in-game missions. While the game is fully playable as a [[single-player]] experience, it also supports up to four-player co-operative [[multiplayer]]. There is also a [[City-building game|town-building mode]] where players can build and upgrade structures that generate in-game currencies and provide combat bonuses to their characters. Unlike many free-to-play games, ''White Cat Project'' has no stamina system.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u3010\u767d\u732b\u653b\u7565\u3011\u30b9\u30bf\u30df\u30ca\u306a\u3057\u3067\u904a\u3073\u307e\u304f\u308c\u308b\u738b\u9053RPG\u300e\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8\u300f\u30d7\u30ec\u30a4\u30ec\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\uff08\u7b2c1\u56de\uff09 |url=https://www.inside-games.jp/article/2014/09/28/81025.html |website=Inside Games |accessdate=11 November 2018 |language=ja |date=28 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Media==\n\n===Video games===\n''White Cat Project'' was released in Japan on July 14, 2014 on iOS and Android platforms. The theme song for the game is titled \"Stand Up!\", performed by [[Yui Horie]]<ref>https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2015/01/06/video-voice-actress-yui-hories-latest-song-stand-up-pv</ref>. An international English version operated from July 23, 2015 until its closure on October 7, 2016. In January 2015, Colopl released a [[Virtual reality|VR]] version of ''White Cat Project'' for the [[Oculus Rift]]. Named ''Shironeko VR Project'', the game can be controlled with a gamepad, keyboard and mouse, or on a smartphone.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Toto |first1=Serkan |title=Colopl Releases Oculus Rift Version Of Mobile Hit \u201cWhite Cat Project\u201d (Shironeko VR Project) \u2013 Kantan Games Inc. CEO Blog |url=https://www.serkantoto.com/2015/01/11/colopl-oculus-white-cat-project/ |website=Kantan Games |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=11 January 2015}}</ref> A spinoff tennis game featuring characters from ''White Cat Project'' was released in July 2016 under the name ''White Cat Tennis''. The \"Punicon\" controls from ''White Cat Project'' are used here as well.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Suckley |first1=Matt |title=After another big year the old guard still dominate Japan's mobile games market |url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/asia/the-charticle/66836/old-guard-still-dominates-japan/ |website=Pocket Gamer.biz |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=23 October 2017}}</ref> A new action RPG tentatively named ''Shironeko New Project'' is announced for the [[Nintendo Switch]], originally slated for release in 2020 in Japan,<ref>{{cite web |author1=Sato |title=White Cat Project Is Getting A Brand-New Title For Nintendo Switch In 2020 |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/07/13/white-cat-project-is-getting-a-brand-new-title-for-nintendo-switch-in-2020/ |website=Siliconera |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=13 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"delayed\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/shironeko-new-project-delayed-to-unknown-date-past-2020/|title=Shironeko New Project Delayed To Unknown Date Past 2020|date=2019-12-13|website=Siliconera|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2018, Nintendo filed a lawsuit against Colopl over five [[patent infringement]]s found in ''White Cat Project''. These include \"the special technology used to operate a joystick over a touch panel\", first patented by Nintendo for its [[Nintendo DS]] wrist strap that Nintendo claims Colopl had used for its \"Punicon\" controls.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Alistair |title=Nintendo Sues Colopl Over Five Patent Infringements In White Cat Project |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/01/10/nintendo-sues-colopl-five-patent-infringements-white-cat-project/ |website=Siliconera |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=10 January 2018}}</ref> Nintendo later added a sixth patent infringement to the proceedings,<ref name=\"nov2018\">{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Alistair |title=Nintendo v Colopl Lawsuit Drags On To Round 4 |url=https://www.siliconera.com/2018/11/07/nintendo-v-colopl-lawsuit-drags-on-to-round-4/ |website=Siliconera |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=7 November 2018}}</ref> and seeks 4.4 billion yen in damages plus late fees, in addition to an injunction on the operation of the ''White Cat Project'' smartphone app.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Chihiro |title=\u30b3\u30ed\u30d7\u30e9\uff0c\u4efb\u5929\u5802\u306e\u7279\u8a31\u6a29\u4fb5\u5bb3\u3067\u8a34\u8a1f\u3092\u63d0\u8d77\u3055\u308c\u308b\u3002\u5bfe\u8c61\u30a2\u30d7\u30ea\u306f\u300c\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8\u300d |url=https://www.4gamer.net/games/255/G025548/20180110052/ |website=[[4Gamer.net]] |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja |date=10 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/the-nintendo-vs-colopl-lawsuit-on-white-cat-project-continues-to-drag-on-to-round-8/|title=The Nintendo vs Colopl Lawsuit On White Cat Project Continues To Drag On To Round 8|date=2019-10-22|website=Siliconera|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Nintendo won the lawsuit as of April 2020, forcing Colopl to change the game's control mechanics.<ref>https://www.siliconera.com/white-cat-project-to-change-control-scheme-due-to-nintendo-colopl-lawsuit/</ref>\n\n===Anime===\nAn anime adaptation of the game, titled {{Nihongo|\"White Cat Project: Zero Chronicle\"|\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8 ZERO CHRONICLE|Shironeko Purojekuto ZERO CHRONICLE}}, which adapts the in-game \"Zero Chronicle \u2013 The first sin\" prologue event, was announced during the Colopl 10th Anniversary event and is scheduled to premiere in April 6, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-12-16/shironeko-project-rune-story-smartphone-game-gets-tv-anime-in-2020/.140885|title=Shironeko Project/Rune Story Smartphone Game Gets TV Anime in 2020|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref> It is animated by [[Project No.9]], with Masato Jinbo directing and writing the series, Yousuke Okuda designing the characters, and [[Taku Iwasaki]] composing the music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-13/shironeko-project-tv-anime-teaser-unveils-staff-cast-title-april-debut/.148979|title=Shironeko Project TV Anime's Teaser Unveils Staff, Cast, Title, April Debut|last=Loo|first=Egan|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-07-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/12/16/shironeko-new-project-provides-details-on-flying-island-guilds-and-anime/|title=Shironeko New Project Provides Details On Flying Island, Guilds, And Anime|last=Wong|first=Alistair|date=2018-12-16|website=Siliconera|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref>  [[Takanori Nishikawa]] and [[Asuka \u014ckura|ASCA]] are performing the series' opening theme song {{Nihongo|\"Tenbin -LIBRA-\"|\u5929\u79e4-Libra-|Tenbin -LIBRA-}}, while [[Rei Yasuda]] is performing the series' ending theme song \"through the dark\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-27/shironeko-project-zero-chronicle-anime-video-reveals-theme-song-artists-april-6-premiere/.155810|title=Shironeko Project: Zero Chronicle Anime's Video Reveals Theme Song Artists, April 6 Premiere|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-01-27}}</ref> [[Funimation]] has acquired the anime series, and will stream the series on its platforms.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=FUNimation|author=Funimation|author-link=Funimation|date=March 19, 2020|title=SPRING SEASON ANNOUNCEMENT Get ready for a journey filled with flying islands, darkness and a group's search for the Great Runes. Shironeko Project ZERO CHRONICLE joins the Funimation Spring 2020 lineup. Learn more: http://funi.to/ShironekoProjectSpring|number=1240669360718352384|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"plainrowheaders wikitable\" style=\"width:98%; margin:auto; background:#FFF;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF;\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Title<ref>{{cite web|url=https://colopl.co.jp/shironekoproject/animation/zero_chronicle/story/|title=Story - \u5404\u8a71\u306e\u7d39\u4ecb\uff5cTV\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300c\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8 ZERO CHRONICLE\uff08\u30bc\u30ed\u30fb\u30af\u30ed\u30cb\u30af\u30eb\uff09\u300d\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|accessdate=April 6, 2020|language=Japanese}}</ref>{{efn|All English titles are taken from [[Funimation]].}}\n!Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = The Land Protected by Light\n| TranslitTitle       = Hikari ni mamorareshi kuni\n| NativeTitle         = \u5149\u306b\u5b88\u3089\u308c\u3057\u56fd\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n}}\n|}\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| rev1 = ''[[Gamezebo]]''\n| rev1Score = {{rating|2.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rich |first1=Rob |title=Colopl Rune Story Review: Why Would You Do That? |url=https://www.gamezebo.com/2015/10/26/colopl-rune-story-review/ |website=[[Gamezebo]] |accessdate=11 November 2018 |date=26 October 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\nOn July 18, 2014, ''White Cat Project'' reached the top of Google Play Japan's ranking of newly-released free apps, four days after release on Android. It reached 1 million downloads six days later, becoming the fastest growing app in Colopl's history.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u30b3\u30ed\u30d7\u30e9\u306e\u300e\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8\u300f\u304c\u7d2f\u8a08100\u4e07\u30c0\u30a6\u30f3\u30ed\u30fc\u30c9\u3092\u7a81\u7834 \uff5e\u30b3\u30ed\u30d7\u30e9\u53f2\u4e0a\u6700\u901f\u3001\u30b5\u30fc\u30d3\u30b9\u958b\u59cb\u5f8c10\u65e5\u3067\u9054\u6210\uff01\u30a2\u30d7\u30ea\u5185\u306b\u3066\u8a18\u5ff5\u30ad\u30e3\u30f3\u30da\u30fc\u30f3\u3082\u5b9f\u65bd\uff5e |url=https://colopl.co.jp/news/pressrelease/2014072801.php |website=Colopl |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja |date=28 July 2014}}</ref> It soon became Japan's fastest growing smartphone game, having amassed 10 million downloads a little more than a month later on August 30.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Toto |first1=Serkan |title=Colopl\u2019s White Cat Project, Japan\u2019s Fastest Growing Smartphone Game, Hits 12 Million Downloads |url=https://www.serkantoto.com/2014/09/13/colopl-3668-white-cat-shiro-neko-project/ |website=Kantan Games |accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref> It reached 100 million downloads on June 27, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u30b9\u30de\u30fc\u30c8\u30d5\u30a9\u30f3\u5411\u3051\u30a2\u30d7\u30ea\u30c0\u30a6\u30f3\u30ed\u30fc\u30c9\u6570\u30fb\u5229\u7528\u8005\u6570\u63a8\u79fb |url=https://colopl.co.jp/ir/library/appdls.html#shironeko |website=Colopl |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja}}</ref>\n\nThe game won the award for \"Best Game of 2014\" in [[Google Play|Google Play Japan]] and in \"Best iPhone Game\" and \"Best iPad Game\" in Japan's [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]] Best of 2014 awards.<ref>{{cite web |author1=ukulele |title=\u3010\u767d\u732b\u3011\u795d\u30fb2014\u5e74\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u53d7\u8cde!! \u3010\u30b8\u30e5\u30a8\u30eb\u3011\u3092\u8cb0\u3048\u308b\u8a18\u5ff5\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8\u958b\u50ac\u4e2d! |url=http://www.appbank.net/2014/12/11/iphone-application/944633.php |website=AppBank |accessdate=12 November 2018 |pages=11 December 2014 |language=ja}}</ref> It also won the \"Excellence\" award in the  [[Famitsu]] Awards in 2014 and 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u201c\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901a\u30a2\u30ef\u30fc\u30c92014\u2033\u306e\u53d7\u8cde\u4f5c\u304c\u767a\u8868\uff01\u30b9\u30de\u30db\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u306f7\u672c\uff01 [\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901aApp] |url=https://app.famitsu.com/20150422_517335/ |website=\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901aApp |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja |date=22 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u201c\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901a\u30a2\u30ef\u30fc\u30c92015\u2033\u53d7\u8cde\u4f5c\u54c1\u767a\u8868\uff01 \u30b9\u30de\u30db\u306f\u300e\u30e2\u30f3\u30b9\u30c8\u300f\u3084\u300e\u767d\u732b\u300f\u3001\u300e\u30b0\u30e9\u30d6\u30eb\u300f\u306a\u3069\u8a086\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u53d7\u8cde [\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901aApp] |url=https://app.famitsu.com/20160510_716841/ |website=\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901aApp |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja |date=10 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://colopl.co.jp/shironekoproject/ Official website]\n* {{Official website|https://colopl.co.jp/shironekoproject/animation/zero_chronicle/|Anime official website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|anime|22323|White Cat Project: Zero Chronicle}}\n\n{{Project No.9}}\n\n[[Category:2014 video games]]\n[[Category:2020 anime television series]]\n[[Category:Action role-playing video games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:Free-to-play video games]]\n[[Category:Funimation]]\n[[Category:Gacha games]]\n[[Category:iOS games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Project No.9]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n[[Category:Upcoming anime television series]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n[[Category:Anime television series based on video games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = White Cat Project\n| image           = WCP2015GuideBook.jpg\n| caption         = Cover of the 2015 official fan book, featuring the three main characters (Hero, Iris and Catra) alongside event-exclusive characters.\n| ja_kanji        = \u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8\n| ja_romaji       = Shironeko Purojekuto\n| genre           = [[Action]], [[Adventure]], [[Fantasy]], [[Magic]]<!-- Note: Use and cite reliable sources to identify genre/s, not personal interpretation. Please don't include more than three genres (per [[MOS:A&M]]). -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| developer       = Colopl\n| publisher       = Colopl\n| genre           = [[Action role-playing game]]\n\n| director        = Ry\u014dji Tsunoda\n| producer        = Hiroki Asai<ref>{{Cite web|author=\u5800\u614e\u4e8c\u90ce|date=2014-11-29|url=http://weekly.ascii.jp/elem/000/000/275/275536/|title=\u300c\u3064\u304f\u308a\u624b\u5074\u306b\u7b54\u3048\u306f\u306a\u3044\u300d\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8\u958b\u767a\u79d8\u8a71\uff08\u4e2d\u7de8\uff09\uff1a\u53ec\u559a\u2605\u30a2\u30d7\u30ea\u795e|work=\u9031\u30a2\u30b9PLUS|publisher=\u30a2\u30b9\u30ad\u30fc\u30fb\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u30ef\u30fc\u30af\u30b9|accessdate=2015-02-07}}</ref>\n| music           =\n| platforms       = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]]\n| released        = July 14, 2014\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = White Cat Tennis\n| developer       = Colopl\n| publisher       = Colopl\n| genre           = [[Sports game|Sports]]\n| producer        =\n| music           =\n| platforms       = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]]\n| released        = July 31, 2016\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Game\n| title           = Shironeko New Project\n| developer       = Colopl\n| publisher       = Colopl\n| genre           = [[Action role-playing game]]\n| producer        =\n| music           =\n| platforms       = [[Nintendo Switch]]\n| released        = TBA<ref name=\"delayed\" />\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = Shironeko Project Hikoujima Kouen\n| author          = Colopl\n| illustrator     = Tsurujirou Matsudaira\n| publisher       = [[Kodansha]]\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| magazine        = Comic Clear\n| first           = July 2017\n| last            = July 2018\n| volumes         = 3\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| title           = Zero Chronicle\n| director        = Masato Jinbo\n| producer        = \n| writer          = Masato Jinbo\n| music           = [[Taku Iwasaki]]\n| studio          = [[Project No.9]]\n| network         = [[AT-X (company)|AT-X]], [[Tokyo MX]], [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]]\n| licensee        = [[Funimation]]\n| first           = April 6, 2020\n| last            = scheduled\n| episodes        = \n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = Zero Chronicle\n\n| author          = Yuichi Tobiyama\n\n| illustrator     = Fuku Kitsune\n\n| publisher       = [[Kadokawa Shoten]]\n\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]''\n| magazine        =\n| first           = April 1. 2020\n| last            =\n| volumes         = 1\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''White Cat Project'''''|\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8|Shironeko Purojekuto}} is a [[free-to-play]] [[action role-playing game]] developed and published by Colopl for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]]. It was initially released in Japan on July 14, 2014. An English-language version was released internationally under the name '''''Colopl Rune Story''''' and operated from July 23, 2015, to October 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Suckley |first1=Matt |title=COLOPL NI winds up development on JRPG Rune Story after just one year |url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/asia/news/64298/colopl-ni-winds-up-development-on-rune-story/ |website=[[Pocket Gamer|Pocket Gamer.biz]]|date=October 28, 2016 |accessdate=11 November 2018}}</ref> A spinoff title, {{Nihongo|'''''White Cat Tennis'''''|\u767d\u732b\u30c6\u30cb\u30b9|Shironeko Tenisu}} was released on both iOS and Android on July 31, 2016, while the upcoming sequel '''''Shironeko New Project''''' will be released on the [[Nintendo Switch]] at a later date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/07/13/white-cat-project-is-getting-a-brand-new-title-for-nintendo-switch-in-2020/|title=White Cat Project Is Getting A Brand-New Title For Nintendo Switch In 2020|last=Sato|date=2018-07-13|website=Siliconera|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref>\n\nAn [[anime]] adaptation of the game's 3rd anniversary event is produced by [[Project No.9]] and set to premiere in April 6, 2020.\n\n==Plot==\nA long time ago, there is an ancient legend revolving around two figures, the White Maiden of the Sky; represented by the White Cat, and the Black Prince of Darkness; represented by the Black Cat. At the same time, a war between the demons and the guardians of light took place, with the demons led by the Black King of Darkness attacking the lands in the sky. The Black Prince however, despite the wishes of the Black King, defied his orders and falls in love with the White Maiden, in hopes that their union would end the war. Both were not meant to meet and love each other as the war ravaged the world around the land and the skies.\n\nSeveral millennia after the war, in a world consisting of numerous isles, a young hero from the Astora Isle encounters the adventurer Kyle and follows him on an expedition on the isle. They meet a mysterious girl named Iris and a talking white cat named Catra, and together they make their way to the isle's ruins, where they find a flying island. Kyle becomes consumed by darkness there, and the party resolves to travel to the ends of the world on the flying island in order to find the seven \"Great Runes\", following Kyle's words before he disappeared.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc\uff5c\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8 \u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8 |url=https://colopl.co.jp/shironekoproject/character/ |website=Colopl |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja}}</ref> Upon their adventures towards finding the Runes, both the hero and Iris start to fill the pieces, meeting friends and enemies and discovering their true identities.\n\n==Gameplay==\n''White Cat Project'' is an [[action role-playing game]] with [[touchscreen]] controls, where the player controls the character by dragging the finger across the screen (a mechanic Colopl calls \"Punicon\") and tapping to attack. Special abilities can be activated by holding the finger on the character, which opens up a selection menu of abilities. All of these actions can be done using one finger only, which facilitates one-handed gaming.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Eugene |title=White Cat Project Is An Action RPG Played With Just Your Thumb |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2014/07/12/white-cat-project-action-rpg-played-just-thumb/ |website=[[Siliconera]] |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=12 July 2014}}</ref>  \n\nThe characters also have their own classes corresponding to weapon types, for example swords, bows, and mage staffs. In general, most characters are gained via a \"Summon\" tab which works on a [[Gacha game|gacha]] system. Runes are spent on randomized characters, with some characters being common and other characters being rare.  Some characters can be gained for free by completing in-game missions. While the game is fully playable as a [[single-player]] experience, it also supports up to four-player co-operative [[multiplayer]]. There is also a [[City-building game|town-building mode]] where players can build and upgrade structures that generate in-game currencies and provide combat bonuses to their characters. Unlike many free-to-play games, ''White Cat Project'' has no stamina system.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u3010\u767d\u732b\u653b\u7565\u3011\u30b9\u30bf\u30df\u30ca\u306a\u3057\u3067\u904a\u3073\u307e\u304f\u308c\u308b\u738b\u9053RPG\u300e\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8\u300f\u30d7\u30ec\u30a4\u30ec\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\uff08\u7b2c1\u56de\uff09 |url=https://www.inside-games.jp/article/2014/09/28/81025.html |website=Inside Games |accessdate=11 November 2018 |language=ja |date=28 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Media==\n\n===Video games===\n''White Cat Project'' was released in Japan on July 14, 2014 on iOS and Android platforms. The theme song for the game is titled \"Stand Up!\", performed by [[Yui Horie]]<ref>https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2015/01/06/video-voice-actress-yui-hories-latest-song-stand-up-pv</ref>. An international English version operated from July 23, 2015 until its closure on October 7, 2016. In January 2015, Colopl released a [[Virtual reality|VR]] version of ''White Cat Project'' for the [[Oculus Rift]]. Named ''Shironeko VR Project'', the game can be controlled with a gamepad, keyboard and mouse, or on a smartphone.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Toto |first1=Serkan |title=Colopl Releases Oculus Rift Version Of Mobile Hit \u201cWhite Cat Project\u201d (Shironeko VR Project) \u2013 Kantan Games Inc. CEO Blog |url=https://www.serkantoto.com/2015/01/11/colopl-oculus-white-cat-project/ |website=Kantan Games |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=11 January 2015}}</ref> A spinoff tennis game featuring characters from ''White Cat Project'' was released in July 2016 under the name ''White Cat Tennis''. The \"Punicon\" controls from ''White Cat Project'' are used here as well.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Suckley |first1=Matt |title=After another big year the old guard still dominate Japan's mobile games market |url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/asia/the-charticle/66836/old-guard-still-dominates-japan/ |website=Pocket Gamer.biz |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=23 October 2017}}</ref> A new action RPG tentatively named ''Shironeko New Project'' is announced for the [[Nintendo Switch]], originally slated for release in 2020 in Japan,<ref>{{cite web |author1=Sato |title=White Cat Project Is Getting A Brand-New Title For Nintendo Switch In 2020 |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/07/13/white-cat-project-is-getting-a-brand-new-title-for-nintendo-switch-in-2020/ |website=Siliconera |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=13 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"delayed\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/shironeko-new-project-delayed-to-unknown-date-past-2020/|title=Shironeko New Project Delayed To Unknown Date Past 2020|date=2019-12-13|website=Siliconera|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2018, Nintendo filed a lawsuit against Colopl over five [[patent infringement]]s found in ''White Cat Project''. These include \"the special technology used to operate a joystick over a touch panel\", first patented by Nintendo for its [[Nintendo DS]] wrist strap that Nintendo claims Colopl had used for its \"Punicon\" controls.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Alistair |title=Nintendo Sues Colopl Over Five Patent Infringements In White Cat Project |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/01/10/nintendo-sues-colopl-five-patent-infringements-white-cat-project/ |website=Siliconera |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=10 January 2018}}</ref> Nintendo later added a sixth patent infringement to the proceedings,<ref name=\"nov2018\">{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Alistair |title=Nintendo v Colopl Lawsuit Drags On To Round 4 |url=https://www.siliconera.com/2018/11/07/nintendo-v-colopl-lawsuit-drags-on-to-round-4/ |website=Siliconera |accessdate=12 November 2018 |date=7 November 2018}}</ref> and seeks 4.4 billion yen in damages plus late fees, in addition to an injunction on the operation of the ''White Cat Project'' smartphone app.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Chihiro |title=\u30b3\u30ed\u30d7\u30e9\uff0c\u4efb\u5929\u5802\u306e\u7279\u8a31\u6a29\u4fb5\u5bb3\u3067\u8a34\u8a1f\u3092\u63d0\u8d77\u3055\u308c\u308b\u3002\u5bfe\u8c61\u30a2\u30d7\u30ea\u306f\u300c\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8\u300d |url=https://www.4gamer.net/games/255/G025548/20180110052/ |website=[[4Gamer.net]] |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja |date=10 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/the-nintendo-vs-colopl-lawsuit-on-white-cat-project-continues-to-drag-on-to-round-8/|title=The Nintendo vs Colopl Lawsuit On White Cat Project Continues To Drag On To Round 8|date=2019-10-22|website=Siliconera|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Nintendo won the lawsuit as of April 2020, forcing Colopl to change the game's control mechanics.<ref>https://www.siliconera.com/white-cat-project-to-change-control-scheme-due-to-nintendo-colopl-lawsuit/</ref>\n\n===Anime===\nAn anime adaptation of the game, titled {{Nihongo|\"White Cat Project: Zero Chronicle\"|\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8 ZERO CHRONICLE|Shironeko Purojekuto ZERO CHRONICLE}}, which adapts the in-game \"Zero Chronicle \u2013 The first sin\" prologue event, was announced during the Colopl 10th Anniversary event and is scheduled to premiere in April 6, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-12-16/shironeko-project-rune-story-smartphone-game-gets-tv-anime-in-2020/.140885|title=Shironeko Project/Rune Story Smartphone Game Gets TV Anime in 2020|last=Hodgkins|first=Crystalyn|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref> It is animated by [[Project No.9]], with Masato Jinbo directing and writing the series, Yousuke Okuda designing the characters, and [[Taku Iwasaki]] composing the music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-07-13/shironeko-project-tv-anime-teaser-unveils-staff-cast-title-april-debut/.148979|title=Shironeko Project TV Anime's Teaser Unveils Staff, Cast, Title, April Debut|last=Loo|first=Egan|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-07-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/12/16/shironeko-new-project-provides-details-on-flying-island-guilds-and-anime/|title=Shironeko New Project Provides Details On Flying Island, Guilds, And Anime|last=Wong|first=Alistair|date=2018-12-16|website=Siliconera|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref>  [[Takanori Nishikawa]] and [[Asuka \u014ckura|ASCA]] are performing the series' opening theme song {{Nihongo|\"Tenbin -LIBRA-\"|\u5929\u79e4-Libra-|Tenbin -LIBRA-}}, while [[Rei Yasuda]] is performing the series' ending theme song \"through the dark\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-27/shironeko-project-zero-chronicle-anime-video-reveals-theme-song-artists-april-6-premiere/.155810|title=Shironeko Project: Zero Chronicle Anime's Video Reveals Theme Song Artists, April 6 Premiere|last=Pineda|first=Rafael Antonio|website=Anime News Network|language=en|access-date=2019-01-27}}</ref> [[Funimation]] has acquired the anime series, and will stream the series on its platforms.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=FUNimation|author=Funimation|author-link=Funimation|date=March 19, 2020|title=SPRING SEASON ANNOUNCEMENT Get ready for a journey filled with flying islands, darkness and a group's search for the Great Runes. Shironeko Project ZERO CHRONICLE joins the Funimation Spring 2020 lineup. Learn more: http://funi.to/ShironekoProjectSpring|number=1240669360718352384|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"plainrowheaders wikitable\" style=\"width:98%; margin:auto; background:#FFF;\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF;\"\n!{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Title<ref>{{cite web|url=https://colopl.co.jp/shironekoproject/animation/zero_chronicle/story/|title=Story - \u5404\u8a71\u306e\u7d39\u4ecb\uff5cTV\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u300c\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8 ZERO CHRONICLE\uff08\u30bc\u30ed\u30fb\u30af\u30ed\u30cb\u30af\u30eb\uff09\u300d\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|accessdate=April 6, 2020|language=Japanese}}</ref>{{efn|All English titles are taken from [[Funimation]].}}\n!Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = The Land Protected by Light\n| TranslitTitle       = Hikari ni mamorareshi kuni\n| NativeTitle         = \u5149\u306b\u5b88\u3089\u308c\u3057\u56fd\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n}}\n|}\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| rev1 = ''[[Gamezebo]]''\n| rev1Score = {{rating|2.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rich |first1=Rob |title=Colopl Rune Story Review: Why Would You Do That? |url=https://www.gamezebo.com/2015/10/26/colopl-rune-story-review/ |website=[[Gamezebo]] |accessdate=11 November 2018 |date=26 October 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\nOn July 18, 2014, ''White Cat Project'' reached the top of Google Play Japan's ranking of newly-released free apps, four days after release on Android. It reached 1 million downloads six days later, becoming the fastest growing app in Colopl's history.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u30b3\u30ed\u30d7\u30e9\u306e\u300e\u767d\u732b\u30d7\u30ed\u30b8\u30a7\u30af\u30c8\u300f\u304c\u7d2f\u8a08100\u4e07\u30c0\u30a6\u30f3\u30ed\u30fc\u30c9\u3092\u7a81\u7834 \uff5e\u30b3\u30ed\u30d7\u30e9\u53f2\u4e0a\u6700\u901f\u3001\u30b5\u30fc\u30d3\u30b9\u958b\u59cb\u5f8c10\u65e5\u3067\u9054\u6210\uff01\u30a2\u30d7\u30ea\u5185\u306b\u3066\u8a18\u5ff5\u30ad\u30e3\u30f3\u30da\u30fc\u30f3\u3082\u5b9f\u65bd\uff5e |url=https://colopl.co.jp/news/pressrelease/2014072801.php |website=Colopl |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja |date=28 July 2014}}</ref> It soon became Japan's fastest growing smartphone game, having amassed 10 million downloads a little more than a month later on August 30.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Toto |first1=Serkan |title=Colopl\u2019s White Cat Project, Japan\u2019s Fastest Growing Smartphone Game, Hits 12 Million Downloads |url=https://www.serkantoto.com/2014/09/13/colopl-3668-white-cat-shiro-neko-project/ |website=Kantan Games |accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref> It reached 100 million downloads on June 27, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u30b9\u30de\u30fc\u30c8\u30d5\u30a9\u30f3\u5411\u3051\u30a2\u30d7\u30ea\u30c0\u30a6\u30f3\u30ed\u30fc\u30c9\u6570\u30fb\u5229\u7528\u8005\u6570\u63a8\u79fb |url=https://colopl.co.jp/ir/library/appdls.html#shironeko |website=Colopl |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja}}</ref>\n\nThe game won the award for \"Best Game of 2014\" in [[Google Play|Google Play Japan]] and in \"Best iPhone Game\" and \"Best iPad Game\" in Japan's [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]] Best of 2014 awards.<ref>{{cite web |author1=ukulele |title=\u3010\u767d\u732b\u3011\u795d\u30fb2014\u5e74\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u53d7\u8cde!! \u3010\u30b8\u30e5\u30a8\u30eb\u3011\u3092\u8cb0\u3048\u308b\u8a18\u5ff5\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8\u958b\u50ac\u4e2d! |url=http://www.appbank.net/2014/12/11/iphone-application/944633.php |website=AppBank |accessdate=12 November 2018 |pages=11 December 2014 |language=ja}}</ref> It also won the \"Excellence\" award in the  [[Famitsu]] Awards in 2014 and 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u201c\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901a\u30a2\u30ef\u30fc\u30c92014\u2033\u306e\u53d7\u8cde\u4f5c\u304c\u767a\u8868\uff01\u30b9\u30de\u30db\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u306f7\u672c\uff01 [\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901aApp] |url=https://app.famitsu.com/20150422_517335/ |website=\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901aApp |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja |date=22 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u201c\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901a\u30a2\u30ef\u30fc\u30c92015\u2033\u53d7\u8cde\u4f5c\u54c1\u767a\u8868\uff01 \u30b9\u30de\u30db\u306f\u300e\u30e2\u30f3\u30b9\u30c8\u300f\u3084\u300e\u767d\u732b\u300f\u3001\u300e\u30b0\u30e9\u30d6\u30eb\u300f\u306a\u3069\u8a086\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u53d7\u8cde [\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901aApp] |url=https://app.famitsu.com/20160510_716841/ |website=\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901aApp |accessdate=12 November 2018 |language=ja |date=10 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://colopl.co.jp/shironekoproject/ Official website]\n* {{Official website|https://colopl.co.jp/shironekoproject/animation/zero_chronicle/|Anime official website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|anime|22323|White Cat Project: Zero Chronicle}}\n\n{{Project No.9}}\n\n[[Category:2014 video games]]\n[[Category:2020 anime television series]]\n[[Category:Action role-playing video games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:Free-to-play video games]]\n[[Category:Funimation]]\n[[Category:Gacha games]]\n[[Category:iOS games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Project No.9]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n[[Category:Upcoming anime television series]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n[[Category:Anime television series based on video games]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toAction(link changed toAction game) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_Cat_Project"}
{"title_page": "Patrick Yaw Boamah", "text_new": "{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix =\n| name = Patrick Yaw Boamah\n| honorific-suffix =\n| image = \n| alt = \n| constituency_MP = [[Okaikwei Central\u00a0 (Ghana parliament constituency)|Okaikwei Central\u00a0 Constituency]]\n| parliament = Ghana\n| majority =\n| predecessor = ''New''\n| successor = \n| term_start = 7 January 2013\n| term_end =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|9|19}}\n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| nationality = Ghanaian\n| spouse =\n| party = [[New Patriotic Party]]\n| relations =\n| children =\n| residence =\n| alma_mater = {{unbulleted|[[University of Ghana]]|[[Ghana School of Law]]}}\n| occupation = [[Politician]]\n| profession = [[Lawyer]]\n| signature =\n| signature_alt =\n| website =\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Patrick Yaw Boamah''' is a Ghanaian politician and member of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|Seventh Parliament of the Fourth Republic of Ghana]] representing the Okaikwei Central Constituency in the [[Greater Accra Region]] on the ticket of the New Patriotic Party.<ref name=\"PATRICK\"/>\n\n==Early life and education==\nBoamah was born on 19 September 1974. He hails from Mourso-Effiduase, in the [[Ashanti Region]] of [[Ghana]]. He obtained his [[bachelor of laws]] and master's degree in International Affairs from the [[University of Ghana]] in 2004 and 2005 respectively. He later proceeded to the [[Ghana School of Law]] where he received his [[barrister-at-law]] degree in 2009.<ref name=\"PBOAMAH\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanamps.com/mps/details.php?id=5483 |title=Ghana MPs - List of MPs|website=www.ghanamps.com|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref><ref name=\"BOAMAH\">{{cite web |url=https://mobile.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/republic/parliamentatian.php?ID=42 |title=Member of Parliament Patrick Yaw Boamah |publisher=Ghana Web |accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"PYB\">{{cite web |url=https://ukgcc.com.gh/hon-patrick-yaw-boamah/ |title=HON. PATRICK YAW BOAMAH |publisher=UKGCC |accessdate=5 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"PATRICK\">{{cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=201 |title=HON. PATRICK YAW BOAMAH |publisher=Parliament of Ghana |accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"PB\">{{cite web |url=http://www.onmaonline.com/hon-patrick-yaw-boamah/ |title=Hon. Patrick Yaw Boamah |publisher=Okaikwei North Municipal Assembly |accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nBoamah is a lawyer by profession. Prior to entering politics, he was an Associate at the Sam Okudzeto and Associates law firm.<ref name=\"PBOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"BOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"PYB\"/><ref name=\"PATRICK\"/><ref name=\"PB\"/>\n\n==Politics==\nBoamah entered parliament on 7 January 2013 on the ticket of the [[New Patriotic Party]] representing the [[Okaikwei Central\u00a0 (Ghana parliament constituency)|Okaikwei Central\u00a0 Constituency]]. He was re-elected in the [[2016 Ghanaian general election]] to represent the constituency for a second consecutive term.<ref name=\"PBOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"BOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"PYB\"/><ref name=\"PATRICK\"/><ref name=\"PB\"/>\n\nIn parliament, he has served on various committees, some of which include; the Subsidiary Legislation Committee, the Judiciary Committee, and the Foreign Affairs Committee.<ref name=\"BOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"PATRICK\"/><ref name=\"PB\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nBoamah is married with two children. He identifies as a Christian and a member of the [[Methodist Church of Ghana]].<ref name=\"PBOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"BOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"PYB\"/><ref name=\"PATRICK\"/><ref name=\"PB\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boamah, Patrick Yaw}}\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Patriotic Party politicians]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix =\n| name = Patrick Yaw Boamah\n| honorific-suffix =\n| image = \n| alt = \n| constituency_MP = [[Okaikwei Central\u00a0 (Ghana parliament constituency)|Okaikwei Central\u00a0 Constituency]]\n| parliament = Ghana\n| majority =\n| predecessor = ''New''\n| successor = \n| term_start = 7 January 2013\n| term_end =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|9|19}}\n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| nationality = Ghanaian\n| spouse =\n| party = [[New Patriotic Party]]\n| relations =\n| children =\n| residence =\n| alma_mater = {{unbulleted|[[University of Ghana]]|[[Ghana School of Law]]}}\n| occupation = [[Politician]]\n| profession = [[Lawyer]]\n| signature =\n| signature_alt =\n| website =\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Patrick Yaw Boamah''' is a Ghanaian politician and member of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|Seventh Parliament of the Fourth Republic of Ghana]] representing the Okaikwei Central Constituency in the [[Greater Accra Region]] on the ticket of the New Patriotic Party.<ref name=\"PATRICK\"/>\n\n==Early life and education==\nBoamah was born on 19 September 1974. He hails from Mourso-Effiduase, in the [[Ashanti Region]] of [[Ghana]]. He obtained his [[bachelor of laws]] and masters' degree in International Affairs from the [[University of Ghana]] in 2004 and 2005 respectively. He later proceeded to the [[Ghana School of Law]] where he received his [[barrister-at-law]] degree in 2009.<ref name=\"PBOAMAH\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanamps.com/mps/details.php?id=5483 |title=Ghana MPs - List of MPs|website=www.ghanamps.com|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref><ref name=\"BOAMAH\">{{cite web |url=https://mobile.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/republic/parliamentatian.php?ID=42 |title=Member of Parliament Patrick Yaw Boamah |publisher=Ghana Web |accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"PYB\">{{cite web |url=https://ukgcc.com.gh/hon-patrick-yaw-boamah/ |title=HON. PATRICK YAW BOAMAH |publisher=UKGCC |accessdate=5 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"PATRICK\">{{cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=201 |title=HON. PATRICK YAW BOAMAH |publisher=Parliament of Ghana |accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"PB\">{{cite web |url=http://www.onmaonline.com/hon-patrick-yaw-boamah/ |title=Hon. Patrick Yaw Boamah |publisher=Okaikwei North Municipal Assembly |accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nBoamah is a lawyer by profession. Prior to entering politics, he was an Associate at the Sam Okudzeto and Associates law firm.<ref name=\"PBOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"BOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"PYB\"/><ref name=\"PATRICK\"/><ref name=\"PB\"/>\n\n==Politics==\nBoamah entered parliament on 7 January 2013 on the ticket of the [[New Patriotic Party]] representing the [[Okaikwei Central\u00a0 (Ghana parliament constituency)|Okaikwei Central\u00a0 Constituency]]. He was re-elected in the [[2016 Ghanaian general election]] to represent the constituency for a second consecutive term.<ref name=\"PBOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"BOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"PYB\"/><ref name=\"PATRICK\"/><ref name=\"PB\"/>\n\nIn parliament, he has served on various committees, some of which include; the Subsidiary Legislation Committee, the Judiciary Committee, and the Foreign Affairs Committee.<ref name=\"BOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"PATRICK\"/><ref name=\"PB\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nBoamah is married with two children. He identifies as a Christian and a member of the [[Methodist Church of Ghana]].<ref name=\"PBOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"BOAMAH\"/><ref name=\"PYB\"/><ref name=\"PATRICK\"/><ref name=\"PB\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boamah, Patrick Yaw}}\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Patriotic Party politicians]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEarly life and education:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: masters' degree \u2192 master's degree", "url_page": "