{"title_page": "Emmanuel Kwasi Bedzrah", "text_new": "{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = Hon.\n| name = Emmanuel Kwasi Bedzrah\n| honorific-suffix =\n| image = \n| alt = \n| constituency_MP = [[Ho West (Ghana parliament constituency)|Ho West Constituency]]\n| parliament = Ghana\n| majority =\n| predecessor = Francis Aggrey Agbotse\n| successor = \n| term_start = 7 January 2009\n| term_end = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1967|5|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Ghana]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| nationality = [[Ghanaian]]\n| spouse =\n| party = [[National Democratic Congress (Ghana)|National Democratic Congress]]\n| relations =\n| children =\n| residence =\n| alma_mater = {{unbulleted|[[Takoradi Technical University|Takoradi Polytechnic]]|[[University of Ghana]]|[[Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration]]}}\n| occupation =\n| profession =\n| signature =\n| signature_alt =\n| website =\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Emmanuel Kwasi Bedzrah''' is a Ghanaian politician and member of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|Seventh Parliament of the Fourth Republic of Ghana]] representing the Ho West Constituency in the Volta Region on the ticket of the National Democratic Congress.<ref name=\"BEDZRAH\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=128|title=Ghana MPs - List of MPs|website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=2019-03-11}}</ref><ref name=\"KWASI\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanamps.com/mps/details.php?id=5392 |title=Ghana MPs - List of MPs|website=www.ghanamps.com|access-date=2020-02-04}}</ref><ref name=\"EMMANUEL\">{{cite web |url=https://mobile.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/republic/parliamentatian.php?ID=37 |title=Member of Parliament Emmanuel Kwasi Bedzrah |publisher=Ghana Web |accessdate=4 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"E K BEDZRAH\">{{cite web |url=https://ukgcc.com.gh/hon-emmanuel-kwasi-bedzrah/ |title=HON. EMMANUEL KWASI BEDZRAH |publisher=UKGCC |accessdate=4 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nBedzrah was born on 28 May 1967. He hails from Tsitso-Awudome, a town in the [[Volta Region]] of [[Ghana]]. He received his [[diploma]] as a Chartered Surveyor from the Ghana Institute of Surveyors. He also received his Construction Technicians Certificate I (CTC I) from the [[Takoradi Technical University|Takoradi Polytechnic]] and a bachelor of science degree in Administration from the [[University of Ghana]]. He holds a master's degree from [[Ghana Institute of Management and Public Administration]] (GIMPA).<ref name=\"BEDZRAH\"/><ref name=\"KWASI\"/><ref name=\"EMMANUEL\"/><ref name=\"E K BEDZRAH\"/>\n\n==Career and politics==\nPrior to entering politics, Bedzrah was the Chief Executive Officer of the Procurement and Project Management Consultancy.<ref name=\"BEDZRAH\"/><ref name=\"KWASI\"/><ref name=\"EMMANUEL\"/><ref name=\"E K BEDZRAH\"/>\n\nHe was elected to represent the [[Ho West (Ghana parliament constituency)|Ho West constituency]] during the [[2008 Ghanaian general election]]. He has been in parliament since 7 January 2009. In parliament, he has served on various committees, some of which include; Works and Housing Committee, and the Standing Orders Committee.<ref name=\"BEDZRAH\"/><ref name=\"KWASI\"/><ref name=\"EMMANUEL\"/><ref name=\"E K BEDZRAH\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nBedzrah is married with four children. He identifies as a Christian.<ref name=\"BEDZRAH\"/><ref name=\"KWASI\"/><ref name=\"EMMANUEL\"/><ref name=\"E K BEDZRAH\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bedzrah, Emmanuel Kwasi}}\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:National Democratic Congress (Ghana) politicians]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n{{short description|Ghanaian politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = Hon.\n| name = Emmanuel K